main event: A civilian observed a jet-like object traveling at high speed in the La Jolla area on 6 August 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 10 seconds before disappearing from view,The civilian estimated the object was traveling at 1,800 to 2,000 miles per hour,The object had three white lights and made no sound,The civilian tried to track the object with his automobile but could not keep up,This event is part of the Project Blue Book investigations.
sighted object: jet-like object with three white lights
witness description: a civilian in the La Jolla area
